subscribeToMicroEvent

public org.json.JSONObject subscribeToMicroEvent(java.lang.String name,
                                                 java.lang.String modulename,
                                                 java.lang.String message,
                                                 java.lang.String callback)
Allows modules to subscribe to a piece of data, in order to get notified when the data changes. Subscribers are called whenever the data has been set, even if the new value is the same as the previous one.

Parameters:
name - Name of the data.
moduleName - Name of the module.
message - message passed to the module when a notification is sent.
callback - name of function to call when a data is changed
Returns:
JSONObject which contains the following values as strings:
  • the actual return value (returnvalue)
  • exceptions (exception)
  • standard out (stdout)
  • standard err (err)
